The visibility of a party or a candidate is important as the visibility of political actors in media coverage will increase their accessibility to audiences, influencing subsequent political judgments. Studies combining media content data with voter surveys have indeed found that voters tend to infer a partyâs political importance from its media salience.

Visibility

The visibility of a party \(p\) in a newspaper \(s\) is defined as the number of news articles published by the newspaper on that party (e.g.Â articles that contain the name of the party), normalised on the total amount of articles by that newspaper in the corpus.

\[ \text{visibility}(p,s) = \frac{\text{#Articles}_{p,s}}{\text{#Articles}_s} \]
